http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: In Health Science 1, students are introduced to healthcare history, careers, law and ethics, cultural diversity, healthcare language and math, infection control, professionalism, communication, basics of the organization of healthcare facilities, and types of healthcare insurance. Students get a good grasp of where healthcare has been, where it's going and how professionalism and personal characteristics impact their success
Academic Foundation

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will know the academic subject matter required for proficiency within their area. They will use this knowledge as needed in their role. The following accountability criteria are considered essential for students in a health science program of study.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify components and solve computations of the metric and household systems of measure.
Calculate mathematical conversions of temperature and weights and measures related to healthcare.
Record time using 24-hour clock.
Recognize and convert traditional numbers to roman numerals.
Define and recognize entry level Medical Terminology and terms related to healthcare.
Communications

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will know the various methods of giving and obtaining information. They will communicate effectively, both orally and in writing.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Interpret verbal and nonverbal communication.
Recognize cultural and religious barriers to communication.
Recognize elements of communication using a sender-receiver model.
Apply speaking and active listening skills.
Recognize elements of written and electronic communication (spelling, grammar, formatting, and confidentiality).
Systems

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand how their role fits into their department, their organization, and the overall healthcare environment. They will identify how key systems affect services they perform and quality of care.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe healthcare history and medical advances.
Identify healthcare delivery systems (public, private, government, and nonprofit) and explain factors that influence them. (including emerging issues)
Describe responsibilities of consumers within the healthcare system.
Discuss common methods of payment for healthcare to include Medicaid, Medicare, TRICARE, private insurance, worker's compensation, etc.
Employability Skills

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand how employability skills enhance their employment opportunities and job satisfaction. They will demonstrate key employability skills and will maintain and upgrade skills, as needed.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Classify personal traits or attitudes desirable in a member of the healthcare team.
Summarize and demonstrate professional standards and characteristics as they apply to hygiene, dress, language, confidentiality, and behavior.
Compare careers within the health science career pathways (diagnostic services, therapeutic services, health informatics, support services, or biotechnology research and development).
Evaluate levels of education, credentialing requirements, employment opportunities, workplace environments, and career earnings.
Legal Responsibilities

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand the legal responsibilities, limitations, and implications of their actions within the healthcare delivery setting. They will perform their duties according to regulations, policies, laws, and legislated rights of clients.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain practices that could result in malpractice, liability, and/or negligence (to include civil law, criminal law, torts, and contracts.)
Describe standards for Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA).
Ethics

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand accepted ethical practices with respect to cultural, social, and ethnic differences within the healthcare environment. They will perform quality healthcare delivery.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Differentiate between ethical and legal issues impacting healthcare.
Recognize ethical and legal issues and their implications related to healthcare.
Identify religious, cultural, economic, and ethnic values as they impact healthcare and demonstrate respectful and empathetic interactions within a diverse population.
Safety Practices

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand the existing and potential hazards to clients, coworkers, and self. They will prevent injury or illness through safe work practices and follow health and safety policies and procedures.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify major classes of microorganisms and explain and demonstrate infection control principles. (hand washing and basic gloving)
Apply personal safety procedures based on Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) and Centers for Disease Control (CDC) regulations and comply with safety signs, labels and symbols.
Apply safety techniques in the work environment to include body mechanics and ergonomics.
Apply standard precautions as described in the rules and regulations set forth by the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) and Centers for Disease Control (CDC).
Practice fire safety related to a healthcare setting.
Teamwork

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand the roles and responsibilities of individual members as part of the healthcare team, including their ability to promote the delivery of quality healthcare. They will interact effectively and sensitively with all members of the healthcare team.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain roles and responsibilities of team members.
Respect interdisciplinary roles of team members and act responsibly as a team member.
Recognize characteristics of effective teams and methods for building positive team relationships.
Collaborate with others to formulate team objectives.
Explore attributes and attitudes of an effective leader and techniques for managing team conflict.
Health Maintenance Practices

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will understand the fundamentals of wellness and the prevention of disease processes. They will practice preventive health behaviors among the clients.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Discuss complementary and alternative health practices.
Discuss behaviors that are beneficial to health and wellness.
Technical Skills
Introduction to procedures for measuring and recording vital signs (temperature, pulse, and respiration). (Students will apply what is learned about TPR and add Blood Pressure in HS2)
Demonstrate use of Snellen chart.
Demonstrate first aid procedures. (Certification optional in level 1)
Information Technology Applications

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Healthcare professionals will use information technology applications required within all career specialties. They will demonstrate use as appropriate to healthcare applications.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Communicate using technology (fax, e-mail, and Internet) to access and distribute data and other information. (including assignments and online assessments)
Recognize technology applications in healthcare.
